Design and develop a voice-operated, touch-based kiosk interface for civic utility services using **Material 3 Expressive** design aesthetics.

## Design Philosophy (Material 3 Expressive)
- **Vibrant & Dynamic**: Use high-contrast colors and large shapes to guide attention.
- **Expressive Typography**: Use bold, large display fonts for clear readability on kiosks.
- **Natural Interaction**: Fluid animations and touch-first hit targets (minimum 64px).
- **Surface & Elevation**: Use containment to group related services.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **API Selection:** For the "agent" feel and multilingual accuracy (especially Indian languages), I propose using **OpenAI (Realtime/Whisper)** for speech-to-text and **ElevenLabs** for text-to-speech. Please confirm if you have API keys for these or prefer an open-source local alternative (e.g., HuggingFace Transformers).

> [!NOTE]
> **Multilingual Strategy:** We will support English and Hindi initially, scalable to other regional languages. UI will be managed via `i18next`.

## Proposed Changes

### Core Infrastructure & Architecture
- **State Management:** Use a central `KioskContext` for navigation and session.
- **Voice Agent Hook:** `useVoiceAgent` for assistant logic.
- **Theme Definition:** Configure Tailwind v4 with M3 color tokens (Primary, Secondary, Tertiary, Surface).

